comment_data.body:
@rhencke thanks for this report. The dev channel version of the plugin catches this type of error and gives you an alternative link to open DevTools, but I'll have to look into the underlying error.

I wonder if it could be a failed installation. Is this happening each time you run an app and look at the inspector tab, even between IntelliJ restarts? If so, please send me your logs (Help -> show log in finder -> idea.log)

Without additional information we're unfortunately not sure how to resolve this issue. We're going to close this bug for now, but please don't hesitate to comment on the bug if you have any more information for us; we're happy to reopen. Thanks for your contribution!

title: java.lang.UnsatisfiedLinkError attemepting to use Flutter Inspector
